on. This is basically the republication variation with the first subject signed omitted. Again, the subject at the end is signed with a head nod. This would result in a verb object subject structure. An example would be: LOVE-CHILD-FATHER, which means "The father loves the child."%0a%3c %0a%3c The last variation is basically a combination of topicalization (1st variation) and null subject (3rd variation). In this variation, the structure is denoted as object verb subject. As like the original topicalization variation, the object is signed with a head tilt and a pause. The rest of the sentence is signed with the subject accompanied by a head nod. An example would be: CHILD,-LOVE-FATHER. This has the same meaning as all the other variations stated before. %0a%3c %0a%3c As we can see, there are many variations of syntax structure is ASL, which is mainly due to the many phenomenons allowed. This led to many different hypothesizations of the most efficient way of syntax. A proposal was to have free order but to accompany the subject and object with specific movements. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: D:)%0a%3c (:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
